[SN]TITLE[SN]
Baby suffers head injury in East Ham moped hit-and-run

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A nine-month-old baby sustained a head injury when he and his mother were hit by a moped as they crossed a road in east London.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The mother, in her 20s, suffered minor injuries in the hit-and-run on Lonsdale Avenue, East Ham on Friday afternoon.
Police said the moped rider was reportedly driving at speed and performing wheelies before the crash.
The baby, who was in a buggy when he was struck, was taken to hospital with non-life threatening injuries.
